theming:
Because we are single-dark with `@theme static` (no light/dark switching), skip shadcn's `:root`/`.dark` + `@theme inline` indirection entirely and define the shadcn semantic color names DIRECTLY inside our existing `@theme static` block in apps/web/src/styles/tailwind.css. `@theme static` emits each token both as a Tailwind color (so `bg-primary`, `text-foreground` utilities generate) AND as a plain `--color-*` custom property on :root, which is all shadcn parts consume. Add, alongside the current tokens:

@theme static {
  /* shadcn bridge - map onto our real tokens */
  --color-background: var(--color-bg);            /* #020407 */
  --color-foreground: var(--color-fg);            /* white/95 */
  --color-card: var(--color-surface);             /* #0A1017 */
  --color-card-foreground: var(--color-fg);
  --color-popover: var(--color-surface);
  --color-popover-foreground: var(--color-fg);
  --color-primary: var(--color-accent);           /* #FFA033 */
  --color-primary-foreground: var(--color-bg);    /* dark text on orange */
  --color-secondary: var(--color-surface-hover);  /* #111A24 */
  --color-secondary-foreground: var(--color-fg);
  --color-muted: var(--color-surface);
  --color-muted-foreground: var(--color-fg-muted);
  --color-accent: var(--color-surface-hover);     /* shadcn "accent" = hover bg, NOT brand */
  --color-accent-foreground: var(--color-fg);
  --color-destructive: var(--color-danger);       /* #DF524C */
  --color-destructive-foreground: var(--color-fg);
  --color-border: var(--color-line);              /* white/8 */
  --color-input: var(--color-line);
  --color-ring: var(--color-accent);              /* focus ring = brand */
  --radius: var(--radius-card);                   /* 0.75rem */
}

Critical naming trap: shadcn's brand slot is `primary`; its `accent` slot is the neutral hover background (dropdown/menu item hover), which maps to our `surface-hover`, NOT to our brand `--color-accent`/#FFA033. Keep the brand as `primary`/`ring`. `warning`/`success` have no shadcn slot - keep using our `--color-warning/success` directly. For a part that references raw `var(--primary)`/`var(--radius)` in an arbitrary value (charts, some rings), add a tiny plain `:root { --primary: var(--color-accent); --radius: var(--radius-card); }` shim, or just normalize that reference during the clean-room copy (we edit each part anyway). Radius: shadcn parts use `rounded-md/lg`; either keep `--radius` and let v4 derive the scale, or rewrite to our `rounded-card`/`rounded-squircle`/`rounded-full` per the flat-pill design. Tune values visually against real content with tweakcn (exports v4 CSS vars), then translate its `--primary` etc. into the aliases above.
